d modules for generating outputs.\n\n**Disclaimer:** This agent is a tool to support medical professionals and should not be used for self-diagnosis or as a substitute for professional medical advice."\n  },\n  {\n    "repo_name": "ny-taxi-workflow-orchestration",\n    "score": 0.031,\n    "summary": "This project focuses on orchestrating data workflows related to New York taxi data. It likely involves collecting, processing, and analyzing large datasets of taxi trips. Workflow orchestration tools like Airflow, Prefect, or Dagster, combined with Python and data processing libraries (Pandas, Spark), would be central to this project.",\n    "readme_preview": "# NY Taxi Workflow Orchestration\n\nOrchestrating data pipelines for processing and analyzing New York taxi trip data.\n\n## Objective:\n\nTo build a robust and scalable data workflow for ingesting, transforming, and analyzing the large volume of data generated by NYC taxis.\n\n## Data Sources:\n\n*   NYC Taxi and Limousine Commission (TLC) Trip Record Data\n\n## Workflow Components:\n\n1.  **Data Ingestion:** Regularly fetch new taxi trip data from sources.\n2.  **Data Cleaning & Transformation:** Process raw data, handle missing values, standardize formats, and enrich with other datasets (e.g., weather, holidays).\n3.  **Data Storage:** Load processed data into a data warehouse or data lake (e.g., PostgreSQL, S3, BigQuery).\n4.  **Analysis & Reporting:** Run analytical queries and generate reports on trip patterns, popular routes, peak hours, etc.\n5.  **Machine Learning (Optional):** Train models for demand prediction, fare prediction, etc.\n\n## Orchestration Tools:\n\n*   **Primary:** Apache Airflow / Prefect / Dagster\n*   **Language:** Python\n*   **Data Processing:** Pandas, Spark (PySpark)\n*   **Database:** PostgreSQL, SQLAlchemy\n*   **Cloud:** AWS / GCP / Azure (for storage and compute)\n\n## Project Structure:\n\n*   `dags/`: Airflow DAG definitions.\n*   `scripts/`: Python scripts for data processing and analysis.\n*   `notebooks/`: Exploratory analysis notebooks.\n\n**Note:** This project emphasizes building reliable and automated data pipelines."\n  },\n  {\n    "repo_name": "password_game",\n    "score": 0.031,\n    "summary": "This repository contains \'The Password Game\'. This is likely a simple game, possibly text-based or a basic web application, focused on password creation or security challenges. It might be implemented in Python or JavaScript.",\n    "readme_preview": "# The Password Game\n\nA fun and challenging game focused on creating secure passwords.\n\n## How to Play:\n\nThe game provides a set of rules and constraints that players must follow to create a valid password. Each level introduces new challenges and complexity.\n\n## Features:\n\n*   **Rule-Based Challenges:** Test your ability to meet complex password requirements.\n*   **Score Tracking:** Keep track of your progress and high scores.\n*   **Simple Interface:** Easy-to-understand gameplay.\n\n## Technologies:\n\n*   **Language:** Python / JavaScript\n*   **Framework:** (Optional) Flask / React\n\n**Note:** This is a lighthearted project for practicing and understanding password complexity."\n  }\n]\n'}
