-making in agentic environments.", "Conducted rigorous testing of model outputs to ensure alignment with defined business logic and safety constraints.", "Managed user authentication and session state within Flask-based web applications for secure AI interactions.", "Documented technical specifications and architectural decisions to support maintainability and collaborative development."] }\n  ],\n  projects: [\n    { name: "Medic AI Agent", bullets: ["Architected a stateful LangGraph flow with custom nodes specifically designed for medical symptom extraction.", "Enforced strict data integrity across all agent state transitions by implementing Pydantic schema validation.", "Extended agent capabilities by integrating external search tools to provide real-time, context-aware information retrieval."] },\n    { name: "MedAI", bullets: ["Developed a Flask-based web application that serves as a robust interface for conversational AI interactions.", "Integrated Google Gemini API to perform complex information extraction tasks from user-provided natural language inputs.", "Implemented a secure user management system to track interaction history and personalize AI responses."] },\n    { name: "Git Agent", bullets: ["Engineered an automated agentic workflow that interacts directly with the GitHub API to perform repository management tasks.", "Utilized Redis and RQ to decouple heavy AI processing from the main application thread, improving responsiveness.", "Designed a modular architecture that allows for the easy addition of new tools and capabilities to the agent."] },\n    { name: "Hospital Agents", bullets: ["Designed a reactive, event-driven architecture using LangGraph to simulate complex hospital environment workflows.", "Leveraged Redis streams to manage asynchronous communication between multiple specialized agents.", "Optimized the system for high-concurrency scenarios, ensuring stable performance during multi-agent task execution."] }\n  ]\n};\n\nconst doc = new Doc