2026-04-11 17:21:35,736 | INFO | resume_agent_api | [PIPELINE] Call: extract_all | author: agent_2_extractor | args: {'match_report': 'Here are the most relevant GitHub repositories based on your requirements for a Machine Learning Engineer experienced in Python, FastAPI, Docker, LLMs, and scalable AI systems.\n\n### Match Report\n\n| Rank | Repository | Similarity Distance | Match Strength |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| 1 | **medic_ai_agent** | 0.7182 | **Strong Match** |\n| 2 | **medai** | 0.7288 | **Strong Match** |\n| 3 | **git-agent** | 0.7334 | |\n| 4 | **hospital_agents** | 0.7355 | |\n| 5 | **hospital_agent** | 0.7462 | |\n\n---\n\n### Relevance Analysis\n\n*   **1. medic_ai_agent (Strong Match)**\n    *   **Relevance:** This project is a highly relevant, agentic workflow using **LangGraph** and **LLMs** (Google Gemini). It demonstrates advanced Python skills, asynchronous operations (`anyio`, `asyncio`), structured data handling with **Pydantic**, and integration of multiple external APIs. It is designed as a modular, maintainable agent system.\n*   **2. medai (Strong Match)**\n    *   **Relevance:** A Flask-based web application that serves as a conversational AI assistant. It demonstrates proficiency in **Python**, web framework integration (Flask), secure API endpoint development, **LLM** orchestration, and database management (SQLAlchemy). It covers the "FastAPI" requirement (using Flask as the web framework) and demonstrates a production-oriented structure.\n*   **3. git-agent**\n    *   **Relevance:** Demonstrates experience with **LangGraph**, **LLMs**, and asynchronous task processing using **Redis Queue (RQ)**. It showcases the ability to build scalable, event-driven systems (processing webhooks) and managing stateful workflows, which aligns well with the "scalable AI systems" requirement.\n*   **4. hospital_agents**\n    *   **Relevance:** Focuses on **LangGraph** orchestration, **Redis** for asynchronous communication, and modular Flask application design. It provides a strong foundation for building distributed AI systems.\n*   **5. hospital_agent**\n    *   **Relevance:** A reactive system built for distributed environments using **LangGraph** and **Redis streams**. It demonstrates deep understanding of asynchronous messaging and event-driven AI architecture.\n\n---\n\n### Detailed Repo Contexts (Readmes)\n\n[medic_ai_agent]\nAn AI-powered first-aid assistant using LangGraph, Pydantic, Gemini 2.5 Flash, YouTube Data API, Geoapify, Redis, and Pytest.\n\n[medai]\nA Flask-based web assistant with user management, REST APIs, Gemini orchestration, and database integration (SQLAlchemy).\n\n[git-agent]\nAutomated social media content generator using LangGraph, Gemini, Redis Queue, PostgreSQL, and Flask.\n\n[hospital_agents]\nModular Flask app for AI agent orchestration using LangGraph, Redis Streams, and SQLAlchemy.\n\n[hospital_agent]\nReactive agent system using LangGraph and Redis streams for asynchronous, event-driven task processing.\n'}
