2026-04-19 08:54:49,058 | INFO | resume_agent_api | [PIPELINE] Call: extract_all | author: agent_2_extractor | args: {'match_report': '| Rank | Repository | Similarity Distance | Relevance |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| 1 | **medic_ai_agent** | 0.7219 | **Strong Match:** Implements a robust agentic workflow using LangGraph and Python 3.10+ to orchestrate LLMs (Gemini). Includes asynchronous operations, structured data extraction with Pydantic, and handles external API integrations—all key components for scalable AI systems. |\n| 2 | **medai** | 0.7329 | **Strong Match:** A conversational AI assistant built with Python and Flask. Features structured medical information extraction, LLM integration, and secure API design, demonstrating foundational skills in building intelligent, data-driven applications. |\n| 3 | **hospital_agents** | 0.7397 | Uses Flask, LangGraph, and Redis for asynchronous AI task orchestration. Demonstrates knowledge of scalable backend architectures required for AI agents. |\n| 4 | **git-agent** | 0.7406 | Features a stateful workflow using LangGraph, Redis/RQ for background task processing, and RESTful API design. This highlights experience with productionizing LLM workflows and building scalable systems. |\n| 5 | **Data-Science-App** | 0.7425 | Relevant context for data-centric applications, though lacking detailed README information for direct technical verification. |\n\n## 🧠 Overview (medic_ai_agent)\nThis project is an AI-powered medical assistant agent, designed to provide immediate first-aid guidance based on user-described medical emergencies. It leverages large language models (LLMs) to process natural language input, extract critical information, and deliver structured first-aid instructions. It uses LangGraph for orchestrating complex interactions, Pydantic for data validation, and integrates with YouTube and Geoapify APIs.\n\n## 🛠️ Tools & Tech Stack (medic_ai_agent)\n- **Language**: Python 3.10+\n- **Agent Framework**: LangGraph\n- **LLM Orchestration**: LangChain\n- **AI / LLM**: Google Gemini 2.5 Flash\n- **Data Validation**: Pydantic\n- **Asynchronous Operations**: anyio, asyncio\n- **Message Queuing**: Redis\n\n## 🧠 Overview (medai)\nA conversational AI assistant for first aid guidance and medical information extraction, powered by Google Gemini and Flask. Features RESTful API endpoints for managing users and chats, structured medical information extraction, and YouTube API integration.\n\n## 🛠️ Tools & Tech Stack (medai)\n- **Language**: Python 3.x\n- **Web Framework**: Flask\n- **AI / LLM**: Google Gemini\n- **Database ORM**: Flask-SQLAlchemy\n- **Authentication**: Flask-Login, Flask-HTTPAuth\n\n## 🧠 Overview (hospital_agents)\nAn asynchronous AI agent built with Flask and LangGraph for orchestrating hospital-related tasks. Uses Redis Streams for asynchronous communication and background task processing.\n\n## 🛠️ Tools & Tech Stack (hospital_agents)\n- **Language**: Python 3.x\n- **Web Framework**: Flask\n- **AI Agent**: LangGraph\n- **Message Queue**: Redis\n\n## 🧠 Overview (git-agent)\nAutomating social media content generation from GitHub commit logs using AI. Employs LangGraph for stateful workflows, PostgreSQL for checkpointing, and RQ (Redis Queue) for asynchronous task execution.\n\n## 🛠️ Tools & Tech Stack (git-agent)\n- **Language**: Python 3.x\n- **Web Framework**: Flask\n- **AI / LLM**: Google Gemini\n- **Workflow**: LangGraph, Langchain\n- **Async Tasks**: RQ (Redis Queue), Redis\n- **Database**: PostgreSQL\n', 'base_summary': '', 'job_description': 'We are looking for a Machine Learning Engineer with experience in Python, FastAPI, Docker, LLMs, and building scalable AI systems.'}
